  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n\r\nThis spec modification: https://github.com/ethereum/eth2.0-specs/pull/44:\r\nThere has been a known bug in which `ActiveState.recent_block_hashes` would not hold the requisite block hashes to validate all potential attestations when it came time during a state recalc. This was due to the list of hashes always being truncated to fit the `2 * CYCLE_LENGTH` requirement even though an attestation could be from longer than that ago when considering large slot skips.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n\r\nSee the spec diff.",
